tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), marked proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or glomerular disease. Hypoglycemia and low HbA1c are noted. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment of renal function and underlying etiology.
